Call for application: Post-doc position proposal

Field of research: natural language processing, text mining, data mining,=
 machine learning

Research project: 3ST (Semantic Highlighter of Scientific Text Corpus)

Supervisors: Fabrice MUHLENBACH and Djamel A. ZIGHED
Starting date / duration: From 1 April 2016 - 12 months

About the project
3ST is an applied research project in which we propose to build semantic =
highlighter of scientific text corpus. With new semantic similarity measu=
res between sentences, we seek to identify and highlight parts of documen=
ts that are semantically and syntactically similar. Through this process,=
 information retrieval tasks and search engine indexing for scientific co=
rpus become more efficient. In this project we want to explore and apply =
a seemingly promising way which is different from other classical approac=
hes (bag of words, statistical weighting methods like TF-IDF). This appro=
ach consists in using a semantic similarity measure between sentences to =
better capture the meaning of the sentences beyond variations in the voca=
bulary and the syntax of the phrases. Our hypothesis is based on the abil=
ity to build an accurate semantic similarity measure between sentences of=
 a text. Once that model is obtained, we will be able to produce a new si=
milarity measure between documents that better take into account the sema=
ntics. The goal is to achieve better information retrieval performance, a=
nd finally to build new text representation schemes to accelerate the res=
earch process.
Our approach, already partially tested on phrases of everyday language, h=
as proven to be very encouraging. It consists in: (1) breaking down each =
sentence in a set of semantic part of speech in the form of triples (subj=
ect, verb, object); (2) using language resources (general or specialized =
ontologies, lexicons and dictionaries) to measure the similarities betwee=
n the same pair of elements contained in a set of triples (i.e., subject =
with subject and verb with verb); (3) identifying statistical variables t=
hat model the similarity between two sentences and (4) aggregating the pa=
rtial similarities between triples in an overall measure between phrases.=
 For the last step of our approach, we use supervised learning methods to=
 determine the optimal aggregation model; that is to say the one which is=
 closer to human experts.
In this project, we are seeking to explore different variations of the fo=
ur points listed above. We also seek to exploit the available collections=
 from the ISTEX platform (http://www.istex.fr/) that aims to provide all =
available means of consultation and analysis now available in all scienti=
fic communities.
The 3ST project is led by a team from researchers of two university labor=
atories; ERIC laboratory at University Lumi=C3=A8re Lyon 2 (venue of the =
candidate) and Hubert Curien Laboratory at the University of Saint-Etienn=
e.

Mission
The candidate will continue the approach developed in the 3ST project, be=
nefit from the corpus ISTEX present on the platform and develop a web app=
lication able to test this approach in the form of a semantic highlighter=
 text.

Job description (activities)
The candidate will follow the objectives of the 3ST project and will prov=
ide theoretical advances in the fields of data mining and machine learnin=
g, knowledge representation, recommender systems and/or virtual communiti=
es.
The other kind of scientific developments expected from the candidate wil=
l be the implementation of a web application. From a query given on this =
web platform (the query consists in one or more target sentences on a top=
ic of interest of the user), we expect that the system will return a set =
of papers from the same area of the user and other scientific areas. The =
semantics highlighting system will also help the reader to focus on speci=
fic parts of the text that are semantically similar to the text of the qu=
ery.

Expected skills
PhD in computer science in the field of natural language processing, mach=
ine learning or data mining, with strong skills in computer development. =
Knowledge in deep learning will be appreciated. Programming languages ski=
lls associated with data analysis and mining (R, Python) and web developm=
ent (PHP, MySQL, Java, JavaScript) if possible:
- Fluent English (written, read and spoken), French is not mandatory
- Knowledge in computer language R and Python, Java if possible
- Website development skills (HTML, CSS, PHP, MySQL, JavaScript)
- Interest in deep learning approaches
- Methods and techniques of natural language processing
- Curiosity, come up with new ideas, be very thorough, think out of the b=
ox
- Ability to work in teams, ability to listen, understand, and communicat=
e.

Benefits (working conditions):
The position is based in Lyon, France, "Porte des Alpes" campus (Bron).
Salary based on qualifications of the Public Service at the University of=
 Lorraine (more than 1800 euros net per month with a possible bonus start=
ing from the 6th month).

Additional information (diplomas, schedules, ...): PhD required.
